`.github/` holds repo-level automation config; today that's exactly one CI/CD pipeline, described fully in `workflows/rollup.ctx`. There's nothing else at this level — no shared scripts, issue templates, or org-wide config — so this directory's contract with the rest of the repo is entirely the deploy workflow's contract.

A typical change here starts and ends in `workflows/`; there's no cross-file coupling at the `.github/` level itself since only one subtree exists.

No intent.md exists for this directory to check against.